{{Infobox officeholder | office = Member of the [[Provincial Assembly of Balochistan]] | term = 2002–2007; 2013–present | party = [[Pakhtunkhwa Milli Awami Party]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1962|12|22}} | birth_place = [[Gulistan, Balochistan]], [[Pakistan]] | alma_mater = [[University of Balochistan]] }}
'''Abdul Majeed Khan Achakzai''' (born 22 December 1962) is a [[Pakistan]]i politician from [[Balochistan, Pakistan|Balochistan]] affiliated with the [[Pakhtunkhwa Milli Awami Party]]. Born in 1962 in [[Gulistan, Balochistan|Gulistan]], he is an agriculturist by profession and is a graduate of the [[University of Balochistan]]. From 2002 to 2007, he served as a member of the [[Provincial Assembly of Balochistan]]. He was elected from the PB-13 constituency ([[Killa Abdullah District|Killa Abdullah]]).<ref name="profile">{{cite web|url=http://www.pabalochistan.gov.pk/index.php/members/profile/en/9/16|title=Abdul Majeed Khan Achakzai|work=Provincial Assembly of Balochistan|accessdate=13 June 2013}}</ref>
In the [[Pakistani general election, 2013|general election of 2013]], he was elected into the provincial assembly again from the same constituency.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/526963/pakhtunkhwa-milli-awami-party-provincial-assembly/|title=Pakhtunkhwa Milli Awami Party Provincial Assembly|work=Express Tribune|date=27 March 2013|accessdate=13 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nation.com.pk/E-Paper/Islamabad/2013-05-13/page-2/detail-6|title=Poll results suggest victory for Baloch nationalists|work=The Nation|date=13 May 2013|accessdate=13 June 2013|first=Bari|last=Baloch}}</ref> He belongs to the Achakzai family of Balochistan, which includes prominent personalities such as [[Abdul Samad Achakzai]], [[Muhammad Khan Achakzai]], [[Mahmood Khan Achakzai]] and [[Hamid Khan Achakzai]].<ref name="profile"/>
== Arrest == On 24 June 2017 Achakzai was arrested because of a hit and run case where a traffic police warden was killed.<ref>[https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2017/06/23/outrage-police-sergeant-run-over-by-mpas-car/ Outrage: Police Sergeant run over by MPA’s car], Retrieved 24 June 2017</ref>
During the course of investigation, it transpired that accused Abdul Majeed Achakzai had also been nominated in another case, FIR No. 156/2009, under Sections 365 and 34 of the Pakistan Penal Code, read with Section 6-K of the Anti-Terrorism Act 1997, lodged with Police Station Satellite Town, Quetta, said a three-page report submitted by Balochistan Police Inspector General Ahsan Mehboob.<ref>[https://www.dawn.com/news/1343069/mpa-achakzai-named-in-2009-kidnapping-fir Outrage: MPA Achakzai named in 2009 kidnapping FIR], Retrieved 4 July 2017</ref>
