{{third-party|date=September 2017}} The '''C. Wright Mills Award''' is a distinction awarded annually by the [[Society for the Study of Social Problems]] to the author of the book that "best exemplifies outstanding social science research and a great understanding the individual and society in the tradition of the distinguished sociologist, [[C. Wright Mills]]."<ref>[http://www.sssp1.org/index.cfm/m/253/ "C. Wright Mills Award"]. ''Society for the Study of Social Problems''. Retrieved 12 April 2012.</ref>
