{{Infobox ethnic group |group = Lebanese people in Qatar |population = 25,000<ref name="bqdoha"/> - 191,000<ref name="joshuap"/> |popplace = [[Doha]] |langs = [[Arabic language|Arabic]] ([[Lebanese Arabic]]), [[English language|English]], [[French language|French]] |rels = [[Christianity in Lebanon|Christianity]] and [[Islam in Lebanon|Islam]] }}
'''Lebanese people in Qatar''' have a population exceeding 25,000<ref name="bqdoha">{{cite web|url=http://www.bqdoha.com/2013/12/population-qatar |title=Qatar´s population by nationality |work=[[bq magazine]] |date=7 December 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222095738/http://www.bqdoha.com/2013/12/population-qatar |archivedate=22 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> and other estimates report a total of 191,000 Lebanese in Qatar. <ref name="joshuap">[http://joshuaproject.net/people_groups/13017/QA Arab, Lebanese in Qatar]</ref> Lebanese people form one of the largest community of non-citizen Arabs in [[Qatar]]. In addition, an increasing number of Lebanese students seeking education and career opportunities opted for the country in light of its relatively reputable institutions across the [[Middle East]]. Most of the Lebanese people in Qatar live mainly in the capital city of [[Doha]].
